      description:
        '\n<figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/0*YmOxfVDvAppvzSl-"><figcaption>Photo by Lissete Laverde on\u00a0Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p>As we race towards the third month of the year, the Xenia team have taken some time to explore some of the top trends that will shape the industry this\u00a0year.</p>\n<h3>The modern traveller desires an experience that will leave a positive footprint</h3>\n<figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/0*UfkEpHN0jZqX-ODI"><figcaption>Photo by Robin Noguier on\u00a0Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p>Sustainability is no longer a trend, it\u2019s a necessity. Guests are more conscious of their environmental footprint. Adopting sustainable practices reduces operating costs therefore increasing profitability, enhances brand reputation, attracts eco-conscious talent, and minimises climate impact. Accommodators that make green operations as one of their core business goals stand to gain market\u00a0share.</p>\n<h3>Creating career pathways for lifelong engagement with the\u00a0industry</h3>\n<figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/0*ObYeCRrUT37p0DHj"><figcaption>Photo by Emma Dau on\u00a0Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p>With a projected talent shortage for the next decade there has been a paradigm shift in thinking from recruit to retain. In an industry, where service and hospitality are paramount, creating career pathways is not only beneficial for the individuals involved but also contributes to customer experiences and brand reputation. It aligns the goals of the employees with those of business, fostering a symbiotic relationship that supports mutual growth and\u00a0success.</p>\n<h3>Personalisation and optimisation through data-driven decision\u00a0making</h3>\n<figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/0*5pHH3EHhFQLJU8H1"><figcaption>Photo by Markus Spiske on\u00a0Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p>The current trend is moving away from simply collecting data to engineering and analysing the vast amount of data efficiently into actionable decisions and gaining an edge over competitors.<br>Implementing robust data-driven decision-making processes requires investing in data collection, analysis tools, and employee training. The benefits are enhanced and personalised guest experiences, improved operational efficiencies and increased revenue, make it a strategic imperative for accommodators looking to stay competitive in the modern hospitality landscape.</p>\n<h3>Contactless technology will continue to be the\u00a0norm</h3>\n<figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/0*BxePEwbEhOQzKC5J"><figcaption>Photo by Jonas Leupe on\u00a0Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p>Contactless technology has become increasingly popular in the tourism industry because of the COVID-19 pandemic. In addition to promoting safety, contactless technology also enhances the travel experience by eliminating the need to stand in line to check-in/check-out, handle physical keys or make payments. According to a research study \u2018Hospitality in 2025\u2019 73% of travellers want hotels with self-service tech. As such, contactless technology is likely to remain a prominent trend for the tourism industry even after the pandemic subsides.</p>\n<h3>Business travel is showing signs of recovery with the bleisure traveller</h3>\n<figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/0*GzYAlwxlSbRzezom"><figcaption>Photo by Artem Zhukov on\u00a0Unsplash</figcaption></figure><p>The recovery of business travel with the bleisure trend indicates a positive shift in the perception of work-related trips. As professionals continue to seek a balance between their work and personal lives, accommodators creating multifunctional spaces with convenient amenities not only attract guests, business travellers and those remote workers looking for a change of\u00a0scenery.</p>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>These trends reflect the ongoing fusion of technology, sustainability, culture and engagement and the changing customer expectations for the tourism industry. It\u2019s crucial for businesses in the sector to adapt to these trends to stay competitive and meet the evolving needs of travellers.</p>\n<img src="https://medium.com/_/stat?event=post.clientViewed&amp;referrerSource=full_rss&amp;postId=7375580a8fc8" width="1" height="1" alt=""><hr>\n<p><a href="https://medium.com/xeniasuite/hospitality-and-travel-trends-predications-for-2024-7375580a8fc8">Hospitality and Travel Trends/Predications for 2024</a> was originally published in <a href="https://medium.com/xeniasuite">xeniasuite</a> on Medium, where people are continuing the conversation by highlighting and responding to this story.</p>\n',
